<dl id="n38214a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38214a">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38214a"> 214(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> sermonette</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Then, with the Jubilate and Apostle&apos;s Creed, the service proceeds. It was preceded by examination of the catechumens and instruction, all the congregation being taught a verse of Scripture, and by prayer; and a special extempore prayer for the new brothers and sisters in Christ follows the sermon &mdash; a not-too-brief catechetical address. (Our congregation does not approve of <mark>sermonettes</mark>, but likes something hot and strong and long.) <small> Rev W.S. Hunt, <a name="WSHI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WSHI"><cite title="source">India's Outcastes: A New Era</cite></a> (1924) 2-3</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c08041a" href="c8all.htm#c08041a">VI.C.08:041(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
